<div id="review_144937687" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/144937687" />
    <a title="Tara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4786401-tara"><img alt="Tara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1295205376p2/4786401.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/144937687?book_show_action=true">Jan 31, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara" href="/user/show/4786401-tara">Tara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer144937687" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11050958413970523891">This is a great trilogy-in-one book for those highly interested in Merlin, King Arthur, and different perceptions of the &apos;Knights of the Round Table.&apos; Jane Yolen weaves a magnificent tale in &quot;The Young Merlin Trilogy,&quot; using her own writing style, imagination, and research to bring the story of Merlin to life in a different way than those before her. He is perceived with more humanity, thus connecting himself to readers as they begin to experience his conflicts and wish the best for his future.</span>
  <span id="freeText11050958413970523891" style="display:none">This is a great trilogy-in-one book for those highly interested in Merlin, King Arthur, and different perceptions of the 'Knights of the Round Table.' Jane Yolen weaves a magnificent tale in "The Young Merlin Trilogy," using her own writing style, imagination, and research to bring the story of Merlin to life in a different way than those before her. He is perceived with more humanity, thus connecting himself to readers as they begin to experience his conflicts and wish the best for his future.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11050958413970523891" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


